<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=2 -->
Bombardier Inc. has issued de Havilland Service Bulletin S.B. 8&hyph;32&hyph;99, Revision `A,' dated July 26, 1993,
that describes procedures for modification of the potentiometer lever stops on the nose wheel steering (Modification
8/1809) on certain Model DHC&hyph;8&hyph;100 and &hyph;300 series airplanes. Accomplishment of this modification
will restore overtravel protection by relocating the potentiometer lever stops. Relocation of the stops will ensure
that excessive fork lever movement is restricted in the event of a mechanical link failure. Transport Canada Aviation
classified this service bulletin as mandatory and issued Canadian Airworthiness Directive (AD) No. CF&hyph;93&hyph;24,
dated September 29, 1993, in order to assure the continued airworthiness of these airplanes in Canada. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Although the effectivity of the service bulletin includes certain Model DHC&hyph;8&hyph;100 and &hyph;300 series
airplanes, Canadian AD No. CF&hyph;93&hyph;24 is applicable only to certain Model DHC&hyph;8&hyph;100 series
airplanes. The service bulletin states that the potentiometer stops on certain Model DHC&hyph;8&hyph;300 series
