<!-- PJG ITAG l=16 g=1 f=1 -->
g=.75(.10)
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
=.075 or 7.5 percent.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Both historical and projected values of ``b'' and ROE are used to estimate ``g.'' Projected values are regarded as
superior, however, since forecasted values incorporate current and predicted changes into the values. In addition,
the use of historical realized book returns on equity in estimating ROE has been criticized because the realized returns
are the product of the regulatory process itself, and are also subject to tests of reasonableness. Therefore, the
Commission's proposed rule requires that the forecasted values of ``b'' and ROE published by Value Line be used in
implementing the sustainable growth method.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 01 -->
