an understatement of the required return. Since most firms pay dividends on a quarterly basis, however, it is proper
to use a method that recognizes such quarterly installments. Such a method applies an adjustment factor to the current
dividend yield to account for quarterly payment of dividends. The dividend yield, assuming quarterly payment of
dividends, is calculated on the basis of the following formula:
