<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In calculating the current price per share found in the denominator of the expression for the dividend yield, an average
price over a period of time, rather than a price on a particular day, is often used in order to remove aberrations from
the calculation. Such aberrations could be the result of events internal to the company (
