<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
Alternatively, under the proposed rule, the DCF model is to be applied directly to the parent company of a subsidiary
carrier where a consolidated capital structure and consolidated system capital component costs are to be used to
calculate the WACC, assuming that the parent company issues common-stock equity which trades publicly.
