<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;20.26 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Adult care assistance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The purpose of the adult care program is to provide non-medical care for eligible adults who need personal care and
supervision due to advanced age, infirmity, physical condition, or mental impairment. Services under this program
can be provided only if they are not available through state, county, local or other Federal programs. Nothing in this
subsection shall be construed to restrict payment of adult care financial assistance pending application and/or
approval for other programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Adult care assistance may be approved when: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The adult or his/her legally responsible guardian applies for such assistance in writing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The adult is unable to meet his/her essential needs, including non-medical care and/or protection, with his/her
own resources. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) There are no other Federal, state, or county public assistance resources, including services provided pursuant
to titles XIX and XX of the Social Security Act, available to meet the required special need. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The cost of care is not available from his/her immediate family. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Facts regarding infirmity, and/or the physical or mental condition of the client and his/her need for non-medical
adult care have been documented. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Adult care assistance may be authorized only if the adult does not require skilled nursing care warranting medical
supervision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Payments shall be authorized under purchase of service agreements only for care provided in state or tribally
licensed/certified group settings, or by individual service providers licensed/certified by a tribe or a state.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) No adult care payment shall be approved for or on behalf of a client until the eligibility case worker certifies
through documentation that all eligibility factors have been met. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
