<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Quality assurance reviews. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The BIA shall establish and perform quality assurance reviews to assess the provision of quality services through
uniform application of regulations. This will be done by performing regular, periodic reviews to determine the degree
to which regulations are followed and implemented in all areas of operation, and to ensure that internal control processes
comply with OMB Circular A&hyph;123. The review shall include operations at Central, Area, and Agency Office levels
to ensure program integrity at all levels. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

